@Fokko Thank you for advice. I squashed my commits. 

BTW, I have a question about Travis CI. We faces an error in `TOX_ENV=py35-backend_mysql` in the build. It seems that other PRs are faced with the same issue. How can we fix the issue?

https://travis-ci.org/apache/incubator-airflow/jobs/334811916#L900

@idlecool  @l1990790120 

There was a [fix](https://github.com/apache/incubator-airflow/commit/181d37321ad08e3b87df2a1f87e16b8b74a24454) made a while back to change from hostname to fqdn, which makes sense since hostname alone isn't always sufficient to uniquely identify a host. So i don't think we'd want to change back to using hostname (if we do, it has to be made all across the codebase)

That said, it's very odd to me that the inconsistency occurred. ti.hostname is stored using socket.fqdn(), but in your screenshot it appears to be only the hostname part.  I suppose this could be possible if (1) the machine the celery worker is on is using a different (older) version of airflow or (2) there are some EMR setting oddity.
